{"ts": "2026-06-07T21:19:53.905046+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my review of PR #1 and `requirements.txt`:\n\n**PR #1** (`interim/torch-2-3` branch) adds an HTML comment marker to `README.md` but does **not** actually pin any versions in `requirements.txt`. The current `requirements.txt` lists all dependencies without version specifiers:\n\n```\ntorch\nnumpy\ndatasets\ntorchtext\ntqdm\nmatplotlib\n```\n\nSince the team has settled on **`torch==2.4.0`** and **`torchtext==0.18.0`**, the following two lines of `requirements.txt` need to change:\n\n- **Line 1**: `torch` → `torch==2.4.0`\n- **Line 4**: `torchtext` → `torchtext==0.18.0`\n\nThe remaining four dependencies (`numpy`, `datasets`, `tqdm`, `matplotlib`) can stay unpinned or be pinned as the team sees fit, but only the `torch` and `torchtext` lines require the specific corrections noted above. These changes should be committed to the `interim/torch-2-3` branch (or the branch associated with PR #1) to align the requirements with the agreed-upon 2.4.0/0.18.0 target.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 487, "prompt_tokens": 4440, "total_tokens": 4927, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 200, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 4224}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 4224, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 216}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "87a28903-b4d8-4927-8cc4-6a799b7f57f0", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea3f4-c767-7e72-90f3-56c3b6777728-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 4440, "output_tokens": 487, "total_tokens": 4927, "input_token_details": {"cache_re